==German==
===Etymology===
Compound of ''[[er]]'' and ''[[heben]]''
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[ʔɛʁˈheːbn&#809;]}}
===Verb===
'''erheben''' (''third-person singular simple present'' '''[[erhebt]]''', ''[[past tense]]'' '''[[erhob]]''', ''[[past participle]]'' '''[[erhoben]]''') ''transitive''

# to [[raise]], [[lift]] (''e.g. arm, voice'')
# to [[levy]], [[charge]]
# to [[gather]], [[collect]] (''e.g. data, material'')
# ('''Anklage erheben''') to [[bring charges]]

'''sich erheben''', ''irregular, reflexive''
# [[rise]] (to one's feet, from one's seat, etc.)
# [[rise]] (''e.g. mountain, tower'')
# ('''s. gegen etw. erheben''') [[rise]] [up] against sth.
# ('''s. über jmd. erheben''') feel [[superior]] to sb.

